# Vue Coding Style

> Extends [typescript/coding-style.md](../typescript/coding-style.md) and [common/coding-style.md](../common/coding-style.md).

## SFC structure

Prefer `<script setup lang="ts">` with ordered blocks: script → template → style.

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
// imports, props, composables, logic
</script>

<template>...</template>

<style scoped>...</style>
```

## Naming

- Components: `PascalCase` file and symbol (`UserCard.vue`)
- Composables: `useCamelCase` (`useUserList.ts`)
- Props / emits: `camelCase` in script; kebab-case in template attributes when needed

## File layout

```
src/
├── components/
├── views/ or pages/
├── composables/
├── stores/        # Pinia
├── api/
└── router/
```

## Style

- Use `scoped` or CSS modules for component styles
- Prefer composables over mixins
- Keep SFCs under ~250 lines; split large templates
